Executive Profile
Kenneth J. Bacon  Co-Founder and Partner, RailField PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships62--
Background

		Mr. Kenneth J. Bacon, also known as Ken, is a Co-Founder and Partner of RailField Partners. Mr. Bacon served as the Executive Vice President of Multifamily Mortgage Business at Federal National Mortgage Association since July 20, 2005. He served as Executive Vice President of Multifamily Mortgage Business at Federal National Mortgage Association. He served as an Executive Vice President of Housing and Community Development of Fannie Mae since July 20, 2005. In 1990, ... he joined Resolution Trust Corporation as director of policy for the Oversight Board. In 1998, he was tapped to lead Fannie Mae's American Communities Fund, directing community development investing, including equity, mezzanine debt and loan participations. He retired from Fannie Mae in 2012. Mr. Bacon served as an Interim Executive Vice President of Housing and Community Development of Fannie Mae since December 2004; as Senior Vice President of multifamily lending and investment in 2000 and as Senior Vice President in charge of its American Communities Fund. Since 1993, he served as a Director of the Office of Securitization of the Resolution Trust Corporation. He spent eight years on Wall Street with Kidder Peabody & Co. and Morgan Stanley & Co. as an officer, where his focus was mortgage finance and related products. Mr. Bacon has been Independent Director of Comcast Corporation since November 2002 and served as its Lead Independent Director. He has been Independent Directorof Ally Financial Inc. since February 4, 2015. He serves as a Director of Bentall Kennedy Management (U.S.) Limited Partnership. He has been Director of Comcast Holdings Corp. since November 2002. He has been an Independent Director of Welltower Inc. since February 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Forest City Realty Trust, Inc since December 05, 2012. He serves as a member of the Board of Trustees for Stanford University. He served as a Director for Fannie Mae Foundation. He served as a Director of National Equity Fund, Inc. Mr. Bacon is awarded the Order of the British Empire for his contributions to the Marshall Scholars program. He holds Master of Business Administration from the Harvard Graduate School of Business, Master of Science in International Relations from the London School of Economics and Bachelor of Arts from Stanford University.Read Full Background




